Senator representing Yobe East Bukar Abba Ibrahim has assured that the remaining Dapchi school girl Leah Sharibu who was held back by Boko Haram during the release of other girls will be freed in no distan time. Senator Ibrahim while reacting to a point of order on the floor of the senate today made by Senator Emmanuel Bwacha from Taraba state also confirmed that negotiations were in top gear to effect the release of the remaining Chibok girls. “I want to reassure the distinguished senator that very serious negotiations are going on and I believe not far from now, she would also be released Insha Allah, the last Dapchi and the remaining Chibok girls,” he said.  Do you have something awesome to share with the world? Click here to share Do you ever have any question about anything you wish to ask and get answer? Click here to ask Follow us on twitter @NigeriaTodayNG Also, Like us on facebook